value.value: A skin disease that is characterized by the painless, continuous peeling of the top layer of skin.

An acquired hemolytic anemia that is characterized by abdominal pain, hematuria, esophageal dysmotility and thrombosis, has_material_basis_in defect in the cell membrane glycosyl phosphatidylinositols that protect red blood cells from the innate complement immune system.
An inherited neural tube defect that is characterized by enlarged openings in the parietal bones of the skull, has_material_basis_in mutation in the ALX4 gene or MSX2 gene.
A mitochondrial metabolism disease that is characterized by growth retardation, microcephaly, hypertonia, encephalopathy, cardiomyopathy and liver dysfunction.
A corneal disease that is characterized by a flat cornea where the radius of curvature is less than 43 D.
An osteochondrodysplasia that is characterized by severe limb shortening and facial dysmorphism.
A syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis, dental hypoplasia, hearing impairment and intellectual disability.
A Ohdo syndrome that is characterized by blepharophimosis, ptosis and intellectual disability and that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the KAT6B gene on chromosome 10q22.
A syndrome characterized by craniofacial, neurologic, limb and ocular abnormalities.

A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by maxillary hypoplasia, stippled chondrodystrophy, flat nasal tip and short columella, and that has_material_basis_in a mutation in the ARSE gene on chromosome Xp22.

A chondrodysplasia punctata that is characterized by abnormal facies and stippling of the limbs, associated with vitamin K-related teratogenicity, has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance.
A syndrome that is characterized by profuse sweating induced by cold ambient temperature.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C2 gene.
A secretory diarrhea that has_material_basis_in mutation in the SLC26A3 gene.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, caused by C4A deficiency.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, caused by C4B deficiency.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C6 gene.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C7 gene.

A complement deficiency that is characterized by deficiency of the alpha subunit of complement protein 8, which causes increased susceptibility to recurrent bacterial infections, especially to Neisseria meningitidis, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C8A gene, which produces the alpha subunit of complement component 8 important in forming membrane attack complexes.

A complement deficiency that is characterized by deficiency of the beta subunit of complement protein 8, which causes increased susceptibility to recurrent bacterial infections, especially to Neisseria meningitidis, and has_material_basis_in autosomal recessive inheritance of mutation in the C8B gene, which produces the beta subunit of complement component 8 important in forming membrane attack complexes.
A complement deficiency that is characterized by recurrent bacterial infections, has_material_basis_in mutation in the C9 gene.
A pigmentation disease characterized by reticulate hyper- and hypo-pigmentated macules in a generalized distribution.
A corneal disease that is characterized by a bilaterally enlarged corneal diameter without an increase in intraocular pressure and that has_material_basis_in mutation in the CHRDL1 gene.
A syndrome that is characterized by bilateral underdevelopment of the external ear, short stature, absent or underdeveloped patellae and severe prenatal and postnatal growth retardation.
A intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal dominant inheritance pattern.
A intellectual disability characterized by an autosomal recessive inheritance pattern.
A syndromic intellectual disability characterized by an X-linked inheritance pattern.
An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the swelling of the uvula to 3-5 times its normal size.

An upper respiratory tract disease characterized by the unusual growth of the adenoid tonsil; has symptom snoring, has symptom hyponasality, has symptom otitis media with effusion, has symptom mouth breathing.
A cheilitis characterized by inflammation of one or both of the corners of the mouth.
A tracheal disease characterized by flaccidity of the tracheal support cartilage.
A lymph node disease characterized by enlarged, non-painful lymph nodes occurring for more than three to six months for which no other reason can be found.
A mouth disease characterized by a white patch on the side of the tongue with a corrugated or hairy appearance; caused by Epstein-Barr virus.

An orofaciodigital syndrome that is characterized by malformations of the face, oral cavity, and digits, has_material_basis_in X-linked dominant inheritance of the OFD1 gene with lethality in males and is associated with polycystic kidney disease.
A lung disease characterized by microbial infection which causes a type of liquefactive necrosis of the pulmonary tissue and formation of cavities containing necrotic debris or fluid.
An acute myeloid leukemia characterized by accumulation of promyelocytes in the bone marrow and by a translocation between chromosomes 15 and 17.
A congestive heart failure characterized by a sudden stop in effective blood circulation due to the failure of the heart to contract effectively or at all.
An intestinal disease characterized by a protrusion of abdominal cavity contests through the inguinal canal.
A intestinal disease characterized by the protrusion by part of the intestine though an opening in the abdominal muscles.
A middle ear disease characterized by an inflammation of the mucosal lining of the mastoid antrum and the mastoid air cell system inside the mastoid process.
A breast disease characterized by a collection of pus in the breast.
A tooth disease characterized by a localized collection of pus associated with a tooth.
A cervix disease characterized by a benign polyp on the surface of the cervical canal.
A spina bifida characterized by protrusion of the spinal cord through an opening, covered by meningeal membranes.
A physical disorder characterized by a defect in the development of the abdominal wall muscles, resulting in the intestines, liver and other organs to remain outside of the abdomen in a sac.
An anus disease characterized by is an abnormal connection between the epithelialised surface of the anal canal and the perianal skin.
A female reproductive system disease characterized by the implantation of the embryo outside the uterine cavity.
An ectodermal dysplasia characterized by abnormal development of ectodermal tissues including the skin, hair, nails, teeth and sweat glands and anhidrotic ectodermal dysplasia with cleft lip/palate.

definition.value: Part of AEC spectrum. Research more.

label.value: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 2

value.value: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the TMEM70 gene on chromosome 8q21.

label.value: mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency nuclear type 3

value.value: A mitochondrial complex V (ATP synthase) deficiency that has_material_basis_in mutation in the ATP5E gene on chromosome 20q13.
